records.addlTxt:
Defendant appears in person in custody with counsel Stephanie Osborne.  Assistant District Attorney, Emily Hynek appeared on behalf of the State.  She will enter a plea to Count 1 in the complaint.  Court reviews the charge and potential penalites.  State has complied with victim notification.  Plea to Count 1, Possession of THC as repeater - guilty.  Deportation warning given. 

Joint recommendation of 1 year probation with conditions to be determined by DOC after assessments are completed.  Court reviews the elements of the charge.  Court performs a plea/waiver of rights colloquy with the defendant.  Defense stipulates to the factual basis found in the complaint to support the plea.  Defendant confirms prior convictions.  Court finds she understands the proceedings and she is freely, voluntarily, knowingly and intelligently waives her right and enters her plea; factual basis exists and she is found guilty.

Per Attorney Osborne, she will be serving a sentence in Monroe county.  Defendant does not wish to speak.

Court adopts the joint recommendation, withholds sentence and places on probation for a period of 1 year with the following conditions:   If agent recommends, defendant must attend and successfully complete a drug assessment, and comply with any recommended treatment.  Defendant to execute any releases necessary for agent to verify compliance.  Defendant to be subject to random testing by his agent.    Not to possess or consume any controlled substances.   Not to possess any drug paraphernalia.  Not to possess any prescription medications of any kind unless those have been prescribed to the defendant by a physician, and in that case, the defendant shall take such medications only as prescribed.  Defendant shall not alter the form of any prescription prior to, or in conjunction with, ingestion.  Not to associate with any known illegal drug users or dealers.  Must comply with all other rules and assessments ordered by probation agent.  Costs imposed and must submit to DNA sample. 

2 days sentence credit granted.   Attorney Osborne is to look into returning cash taken as evidence from the defendant.
Pre-trial conference on May 2, 2018 at 10:00 am.
Attorney Osborne requested that this case track with 18CM68.  Cannot track as this case is assigned to Judge Goodman and 18CM68 is assigned to Judge Becker.
